        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2022-01-10 19:57:14.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\n> Patch Set 5:\n> \n> > Patch Set 5:\n> > \n> > (7 comments)\n> > \n> > Could you explain why you need a separate 'root operation' ?! Its not clear from this commit. Maybe its part of the 2nd part of this user story but I would like to have some idea now...\n> \n> I can see a bit of differentiation in the original stud re 'root' update and non-root udpates but I final to see the exact need. ie. what changed your mind?!\n\nI changed the implementation again. I was not happy with the first implementation because \n- the operation was tightly coupled with the notification feature\n- it was confusing too. For example, the create action was sending UPDATE operation to notification Service. \n\nThe Second Implementation, which Toine reviewed, was a little better because it was less confusing. But, it added lots of if/else to identify if it is root or non-root. Operation enum was also a little confusing as CHILD_NODE_CREATA becomes 'update' inside the enum itself.\n\nIn the latest implementation ( Third approach :) ), the operation and the action method in the dataServiceImpl class are in sync. Also, the logic to identify 'root' or 'non-root' has been moved at one place in NotificationService.\n\nLet me know if you have other ideas to make the implementation better.",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
